---
layout: fullsize
css: homepage.css
title: Home
permalink: /
---

<div class="homepage-title">
	<h1 class="no-margin">{{ site.author }}</h1>
	<p class="homepage-tagline">{{ site.tagline }}</p>
</div>

<div class="image-shadow homepage-photo-container">
	<img
		class="homepage-photo"
		sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px"
		srcset="/assets/images/bonsai-300.jpg 300w,
				/assets/images/bonsai-600.jpg 600w,
				/assets/images/bonsai-1200.jpg 1200w,
				/assets/images/bonsai.jpg 1800w"
		src="/assets/images/bonsai.jpg"
		alt="Bonsai"
/>
</div>

<article class="homepage-about-me" {{ site.animationDelay }}>
	<h2>About Me</h2>
	<p>
		I’m a Front-End Web Developer and Designer from Hamburg, Germany. I love
		design and art, reading books, listening to podcasts, creating Sketchnotes,
		taking photos, and writing Haiku.
	</p>
	<p>{%- more "Read more about me", "/about/" -%}</p>
</article>

<article class="homepage-what-i-do" {{ site.animation }}>
	<h2>What I Do</h2>
	<div class="homepage-what-i-do-text">
		<p>
			I create beautiful, user-centric layouts for devices of all
			sizes on the web for nearly two decades and love bringing simplicity and
			minimalism to everything&nbsp;I&nbsp;create.
		</p>
		<p>
			I deeply care about good user experience: Writing good text, choosing the
			right photography, typography, and colors. Programming fast, reusable,
			well-tested, and easy-to-maintain code or creating
			engaging&nbsp;animations.
		</p>
		<p>
			I am working at <a href="https://www.new-work.se/" {{ site.external }}>NEW WORK SE</a>
			on the Design&nbsp;System of <a href="https://www.xing.com/" {{ site.external | safe }}>XING</a>,
			the largest business network in	Europe.
		</p>
		<p>
			I love innovating: in one of the companies’ <em>Hackweeks</em> I was part of a
			small team creating a new job platform for freelancers. I am
			also a three-time winner of the <em>Prototyping Days</em>, a
			two-day company-wide prototyping&nbsp;event every year.
		</p>
		<p>{%- more "See what I do", "/projects/" -%}</p>
	</div>
</article>

<article class="homepage-journal">
	<div {{ site.animation }}>
		<h2>Journal</h2>
		<div class="homepage-journal-introduction">
			<div class="homepage-journal-text">
				<p>
					I am writing essays about topics including programming, design, self-improvement, philosophy, productivity, books, and films in this Journal.
				</p>
				<p>
					Stay up to date. Subscribe to my <a href="/index.xml">RSS feed</a>.
				</p>
				<p>{%- more "See all Journal Entries", "/journal/" -%}
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="homepage-journal-subscribe">
				<h3>Recommendations</h3>
				<p>
					I’m posting interesting things I find in a collection on <a href="https://raindrop.io/kogakure/recommendations-25041238" {{ site.external | safe }}>Raindrop.io</a>.
					You can follow the collection via <a href="{{ site.url }}/feed-raindrop.xml" {{ site.external | safe }}>RSS feed</a>.
					I publish my <a href="https://readwise.io/@kogakure" {{ site.external | safe }}>Favorite Readwise Highlights</a>.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</article>

<div class="homepage-journal-latest" {{ site.animation }}>
	<article class="homepage-journal-featured">
		<h3>Featured</h3>
		<ul>
			{% set featuredPosts = collections.liveFeatured %}
			{% for feature in featuredPosts.slice(0, 7) %}
				<li>
					<a href="{{ feature.url }}">{{ feature.data.title }}</a>
				</li>
			{% endfor %}
		</ul>
	</article>

	<article class="homepage-journal-latest-posts" {{ site.animation }}>
		<h3>Latest Essays</h3>
		<ul class="homepage-journal-latest-posts-grid">
			{% set latestPosts = collections.livePosts %}
			{% for post in latestPosts.slice(0, 13) %}
				<li>
					<a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a>
				</li>
			{% endfor %}
		</ul>
	</article>
</div>
